surveyDefinition:
{
 "pages": [
  {
   "category": "General Info",
   "elements": [
    {
     "type": "html",
     "name": "question2",
     "html": "<b>When to File a UI Claim</b></br>\nYou should submit an application for unemployment insurance (UI) during the week your employment status has changed.  Some of those changes include:\n<ul>\n   <li>You quit or were terminated from your job</li>\n   <li>Your hours were reduced</li>\n   <li>You are temporarily or permanently laid off</li>\n</ul></br>\nNote: <em>You will not be able to report a future separation date on the application.</em></br></br>\n<b>Minimum Eligibility Requirements:</b></br>\n<ul>\n   <li>You are totally or partially unemployed</li>\n   <li>You are unemployed through no fault of your own</li>\n   <li>You have worked and earned a certain amount of wages in Iowa in the last 18 months</li>\n   <ul>\n      <li>If you have worked in another state and have not worked in Iowa in the last 18 months, you must contact the unemployment office in the state(s) where you have worked</li>\n   </ul>\n   <li>You are able to work and available for work</li>\n</ul>\n</br>\n<b>Important Information You Might Need to File an Unemployment Insurance (UI) Claim</b></br>\n<ul>\n   <li>Your social security number (SSN)</li>\n   <li>Name, payroll address, work location and phone number of your last/current employer</li>\n   <li>Start and end dates of your employment</li>\n   <li>You may be asked to provide details about your employment status and ability to work</li>\n   <li>Name(s), SSN, date of birth, and relationship of any dependents that you claim on your income tax return</li>\n   <li>\n      DD-214 Certificate of Release or Discharge from Active Duty (Member Copy 4) form information, if you served in the U.S. military during the last 18 months \n      <ul>\n         <li>Note: If you do not have your DD-214 at this time, you may be required to provide it in the future</li>\n      </ul>\n   </li>\n   <li>Standard Form 8 Notice to Federal Employee about Unemployment Insurance (SF-8) or Standard Form 50 Notification of Personnel Action (SF-50), if you worked for the federal government in the last 18 months </li>\n   <li>Information about your pension, severance pay, and workers' compensation (ex. effective date, amount, name of employer, etc.) </li>\n   <li>Your A/Alien/USCIS/I94 number and the immigration document name/type, if not a U.S. citizen </li>\n   <li>The name and local number of your labor union hiring hall </li>\n</ul>\n</br>\n<b>The Application Process </b> </br>\n<ul>\n   <li>The information you enter on this application will be saved until 11:59 p.m. on Saturday <<saturdayAfterEffectiveDate>>, if you do not submit the application today </li>\n   <li>You will be logged out of the application if there is no activity for <<initialClaimTimeoutMinutes>> minutes </li>\n   <li>It takes approximately 30 minutes to complete the application </li>\n   <li>You may be required to verify your identity during the application process </li>\n</ul></br>\n<b>After you successfully submit the application, you will: </b> </br>\n<ul>\n   <li>Be able to print a claim application summary for your records</li>\n   <li>Receive a claim confirmation number</li>\n   <li>Receive instructions for filing a weekly claim</li>\n   <li>\n      Receive a link to the UI Handbook that outlines your rights and responsibilities\n      <ul>\n         <li>\n            We recommend you review the UI Handbook before filing for UI benefits by clicking \n\t\t\there: <a style=\"color:#337ab7;text-decoration:underline;background-color:white;padding:0px !important;font-weight:bold;font-size:inherit !important;\" href=\"<<uiHandBookURL>>\" target=\"_blank\">Unemployment Insurance Handbook</a> </br>\n            The UI Handbook explains your rights and responsibilities for claiming UI benefits. It answers common questions and covers general UI information.\n         </li>\n      </ul>\n   </li>\n</ul>\n</br>\n<b>WARNING:</b> </br>\nYou may be guilty of fraud if you make false statements, provide false information, or knowingly withhold information for the purpose of receiving benefits. If you commit UI fraud, you may be fined, penalized, and criminally prosecuted. You will be required to repay UI benefits you are not eligible to receive. If you have an overpayment as a result of fraud, you will not receive UI benefits until you have paid your debt in full. </br></br>\n\n <b>Equal Opportunity is the Law</b></br>\n<ul style=\"padding:0px;margin:0px;\">\n<li style=\"display:inline;\"><a style=\"color:#337ab7;text-decoration:underline;padding:0px !important;font-size:inherit !important;\" href=\"<<equalOpportunityLawURLEnglish>>\" target=\"_blank\">English</a> | </li>\n<li style=\"display:inline;\"><a style=\"color:#337ab7;text-decoration:underline;padding:0px !important;font-size:inherit !important;\" href=\"<<equalOpportunityLawURLDeutsch>>\" target=\"_blank\">Deutsch</a> | </li>\n<li style=\"display:inline;\"><a style=\"color:#337ab7;text-decoration:underline;padding:0px !important;font-size:inherit !important;\" href=\"<<equalOpportunityLawURLBosanski>>\" target=\"_blank\">Bosanski</a> | </li>\n<li style=\"display:inline;\"><a style=\"color:#337ab7;text-decoration:underline;padding:0px !important;font-size:inherit !important;\" href=\"<<equalOpportunityLawURLArabic>>\" target=\"_blank\">&#x0644;&#x0639;&#x0631;&#x0628;&#x064A;&#x0629;</a> | </li>\n  <li style=\"display:inline;\"><a style=\"color:#337ab7;text-decoration:underline;padding:0px !important;font-size:inherit !important;\" href=\"<<equalOpportunityLawURLChinese>>\" target=\"_blank\">&#x7E41;&#x9AD4;&#x4E2D;&#x6587;</a> | </li>\n  <li style=\"display:inline;\"><a style=\"color:#337ab7;text-decoration:underline;padding:0px !important;font-size:inherit !important;\" href=\"<<equalOpportunityLawURLFrench>>\" target=\"_blank\">Fran&#x00E7;ais</a> | </li>\n  <li style=\"display:inline;\"><a style=\"color:#337ab7;text-decoration:underline;padding:0px !important;font-size:inherit !important;\" href=\"<<equalOpportunityLawURLHakha>>\" target=\"_blank\">Hakha</a> | </li>\n  <li style=\"display:inline;\"><a style=\"color:#337ab7;text-decoration:underline;padding:0px !important;font-size:inherit !important;\" href=\"<<equalOpportunityLawURLKorean>>\" target=\"_blank\">&#xD55C;&#xAD6D;&#xC5B4;</a> | </li>\n  <li style=\"display:inline;\"><a style=\"color:#337ab7;text-decoration:underline;padding:0px !important;font-size:inherit !important;\" href=\"<<equalOpportunityLawURLLao>>\" target=\"_blank\">&#x0EA5;&#x0EB2;&#x0EA7;</a> | </li>\n  <li style=\"display:inline;\"><a style=\"color:#337ab7;text-decoration:underline;padding:0px !important;font-size:inherit !important;\" href=\"<<equalOpportunityLawURLSpanish>>\" target=\"_blank\">Espa&#x00F1;ol</a> | </li>\n  <li style=\"display:inline;\"><a style=\"color:#337ab7;text-decoration:underline;padding:0px !important;font-size:inherit !important;\" href=\"<<equalOpportunityLawURLVietnamese>>\" target=\"_blank\">Ti&#x1EBF;ng Vi&#x1EC7;t</a> | </li>\n  <li style=\"display:inline;\"><a style=\"color:#337ab7;text-decoration:underline;padding:0px !important;font-size:inherit !important;\" href=\"<<equalOpportunityLawURLKaren>>\" target=\"_blank\">Karen</a> | </li>\n  <li style=\"display:inline;\"><a style=\"color:#337ab7;text-decoration:underline;padding:0px !important;font-size:inherit !important;\" href=\"<<equalOpportunityLawURLBurmese>>\" target=\"_blank\">Burmese</a></li>\n</ul>"
    }
   ],
